    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-10T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-10T22:00:00-05:00" n="166"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d166">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.34 Leasing/9: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Boal</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-10T21:00:00-06:00"
                            >August 10, 1937—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 11—9:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>219. Department’s circular telegram August 9, 6 p.m. I have today communicated to
                    General Hay<note n="7" xml:id="d166fn7">Eduardo Hay, Mexican Minister for
                        Foreign Affairs.</note> the three points given in your telegram and made it
                    clear to him that these were given to avoid any possible misconception arising
                    out of press reports.</p>
                <p>The General had no official comment to make but told me entirely personally that
                    he could foresee that if West Coast nations of South America availed of the
                    opportunity to secure American destroyers the Japanese and some European nations
                    would sit up and take notice. He wondered whether it would serve as a precedent
                    for the furnishing of European war vessels to the contending factions in
                        Spain.<note n="8" xml:id="d166fn8">See <ref target="frus1937v01#pg_215">vol.
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp. 215</ref> ff.</note> If the
                    opportunity were availed of by numerous Latin American Republics he foresaw the
                    possibility of complications.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Boal</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
